T1  - Time-varying risk premia and forecastable returns in futures markets
AU  - Bessembinder, Hendrik
AU  - Chan, Kalok
JO  - Journal of Financial Economics
VL  - 32
IS  - 2
SP  - 169
EP  - 193
PY  - 1992
DA  - 1992/10/01/
SN  - 0304-405X
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-405X(92)90017-R
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304405X9290017R
AB  - We document that instrumental variables known to possess forecast power in equity and bond markets (Treasury bill yields, equity dividend yields, and the ‘junk’ bond premium) also possess forecast power for prices in agricultural, metals, and currency futures markets. The pattern of forecastability in futures is consistent with economic equilibrium as embodied by a two-‘latent-variable’ model. We test whether the latent variables that explain these futures returns coincide with latent variables that explain returns on size-ranked equity portfolios. This hypothesis is rejected, suggesting that futures are subject to different sources of priced risk than are equities.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - Do outside directors monitor managers?: Evidence from tender offer bids
AU  - Byrd, John W.
AU  - Hickman, Kent A.
JO  - Journal of Financial Economics
VL  - 32
IS  - 2
SP  - 195
EP  - 221
PY  - 1992
DA  - 1992/10/01/
SN  - 0304-405X
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-405X(92)90018-S
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304405X9290018S
AB  - Examining 128 tender offer bids made from 1980 through 1987, we categorize outside directors as either independent of or having some affiliation with managers, and find that bidding firms on which independent outside directors hold at least 50% of the seats have significantly higher announcement-date abnormal returns than other bidders. However, the relationship between bidding firms' abnormal stock returns and the proportion of board seats held by independent outside directors is nonlinear, suggesting it is possible to have too many independent outside directors. All results are lost if the traditional inside-outside board classification method is used.
ER  - 

